Subject: rPSA-2010-0066-1 samba samba-client samba-server
	samba-swat

rPath Security Advisory: 2010-0066-1
Published: 2010-10-17
Products:
    rPath Appliance Platform Linux Service 2
    rPath Linux 2

Rating: Severe
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote System User Deterministic Privilege Escalation
Updated Versions:
    samba=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/3.0.33-1.4-1
    samba-client=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/3.0.33-1.4-1
    samba-server=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/3.0.33-1.4-1
    samba-swat=conary.rpath.com@rpl:2/3.0.33-1.4-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-3237

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2010-2063
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2010-3069

Description:
    Two flaws have been fixed in samba, the most severe of which could
    allow remove attackers to execute arbitrary code on a server
    with the permissions of the smbd process.

